Task: Implement run_tests() — main orchestration function

Summary:
Implemented the run_tests() function in src/gd_tools/test_runner.py that
orchestrates the full GUT test lifecycle via Godot CLI. The function:
1. Finds project root via find_project_root()
2. Checks GUT is installed via check_gut_installed()
3. Finds Godot binary via find_godot()
4. Creates .gd-tools/ directory if missing
5. Builds GUT args via build_gut_args()
6. Sets GD_TOOLS_COVERAGE_ACTIVE=1 env var when coverage=True
7. Invokes Godot via run_godot()
8. Handles subprocess.TimeoutExpired → GdToolsError (exit code 2)
9. Handles non-zero Godot exit → GdToolsError (exit code 2)
10. Parses JUnit XML via parse_junit_xml()
11. Assembles TestResult with all fields
12. Sets coverage_data_path when coverage=True
13. Raises TestFailureError when tests fail and no_exit_code=False (exit code 1)

Files changed:
- src/gd_tools/test_runner.py: Added imports (subprocess, GdToolsConfig,
  find_project_root, TestFailureError, find_godot, run_godot). Added
  run_tests() function (~120 lines with docstring).
- tests/unit/test_test_runner.py: Added 12 unit tests for run_tests()
  covering: GUT not installed, Godot not found, correct args passed to
  run_godot, stdout/stderr capture, TestResult assembly, all-pass no error,
  test failures raise TestFailureError, no_exit_code=True suppresses error,
  timeout raises GdToolsError, non-zero exit raises GdToolsError, .gd-tools
  dir creation, junit_xml_path set correctly.

